# Refresh Browser After Completing Tasks

When you finish a task that changes the frontend (UI, styles, components, assets):

1. **Refresh the browser** so the user sees the updated app.
   - If MCP browser tools are available: navigate to the app URL (e.g. `http://localhost:5173/`) or trigger a refresh so the page reloads.
   - If not: at the end of your response, briefly remind the user to refresh (e.g. "Refresh the browser (Cmd+Shift+R) to see the changes.").

2. Do this **after each "done" / completed prompt** so the latest code is visible without the user having to remember to refresh.

Keep the reminder short and at the end of your reply when you don't have browser automation available.
